  "id": "PLACE_riftglass_hollow",
  "label": "Riftglass Hollow",
  "description": "Riftglass Hollow is a basalt cave carved by ancient impacts and later scoured smooth by ash-laden winds that drive grit deep into every seam. Its walls bear a vitreous glaze of fused slag that catches Vespera Tertius’ bruise-colored auroral spill, turning the interior into a dull, shifting violet sheen. The floor forms a shallow basin of compacted ash and black glass shards, interrupted by narrow fissures that exhale cold, mineral-tainted air. Vox signals degrade sharply within the hollow, as if the stone itself absorbs and scatters transmission into static.",
